description:
Origin

Chalkis was once a human living in medieval Italy. Although she was in love with Alastor, she rejected his advances. One day, curious as to why she would reject him, Alastor spied on her. He discovered that Chalkis was regularly molested by her father and brother. Having discovered her secret, he deviced a plan with her to take revenge on her family. He killed her brother and she fed him to her father, who choked when he discovered he had been eating his son.
name: Chalkis

deck: A young woman who was granted superhuman abilities by the magician known as the Weaver.
description:
Creation

Hydra is created by Paul Kupperberg and Rick Hoberg in Power Girl # 2 (July 1988).

History

In Post-Crisis continuity, Hydra (whose real name is unknown) was a young woman who was granted superhuman abilities by the magician known as the Weaver, who is 45,000 years old. She was one of several selected villains to fight Power Girl. Hydra and Power Girl fought each other in the center of Manhattan and Hydra used his powers to keep their feet Power Girl. However, he was unable to defeat and quickly disappeared from the battle.

Powers and Abilities

Hydra could manipulate the movement and flow of liquid material, mainly water (Hydrokinesis). She demonstrated her skill with the ability to break the network of open water, takes fire and gasoline tanks.
name: Hydra

description:
Creation

Pyro was created by Paul Kupperberg and Rick Hoberg in Power Girl # 2 (July 1988 ).

History

In Post-Crisis continuity, Pyro was a young man who was granted superhuman abilities by the magician known as the Weaver (who had 45,000 years old). Pyro was one of several selected to fight villains Power Girl .Pyro Girl Power tracked and attacked at the door of his apartment in Manhattan.Their fight was taken to the roof of an adjacent building and Pyro launched a concentrated burst of plasma that caused the building to collapse. When Power Girl finally left, Pyro was gone.

Powers and Abilities

He has the superhuman ability of Pyro of the Pyrokinesis.
name: Pyro
